SUMMARY:Billy Gardell: The Less Is More Tour
DESCRIPTION:April 11\, 2026\nPURCHASE TICKETS HERE  \nDoors 6pm/ Show 7pm\nAges: 12+ \n\nBlack Friday Offer!\n(Happening: November 28 – December 5)\nGet into the spirit of giving with our exclusive Black Friday Offer — 25% OFF your purchase! Simply use the password GIFT at checkout to unlock your savings. The offer begins November 28 at 12:00 AM (local time) and ends December 5 at 11:59 PM (local time) and is only available while supplies last. Don’t miss your chance to treat yourself — or someone special — to something extraordinary this holiday season! \n\n___________________________________________________________________________________________ \nBilly Gardell currently stars in the hit CBS series Bob Hearts Abishola\, created by award-winning executive producer and writer Chuck Lorre. Bob Hearts Abishola is a heartwarming love story about a middle-aged compression-sock businessman from Detroit who unexpectedly falls for his cardiac nurse\, a Nigerian immigrant\, while recovering from a heart attack. Undaunted by Abishola’s lack of initial interest—or the vast differences in their backgrounds—Bob is determined to win her heart\, in this comedic and insightful look at immigrant life in America. \nPrior to Bob Hearts Abishola\, Gardell starred as Officer Mike Biggs in the CBS hit series Mike & Molly (2010–2016)\, which continues to air in syndication. He also appeared as Col. Tom Parker in the CMT series Sun Records and held a recurring role on another CBS favorite\, Young Sheldon. \nIn 2016\, Gardell earned a Daytime Emmy nomination for Best Game Show Host for Monopoly Millionaires Club. \nBefore Mike & Molly\, he co-starred in the critically acclaimed series Lucky\, and his additional television credits include Yes\, Dear\, Judging Amy\, My Name Is Earl\, The Practice\, Monk\, and Gary the Rat. \nGardell made his major motion-picture debut alongside Anthony Quinn and Sylvester Stallone in Avenging Angelo\, and shared a memorable scene with Billy Bob Thornton in the Coen Brothers’ Bad Santa. His other film credits include You\, Me & Dupree. \nA veteran of the stand-up circuit\, Gardell took the long road to Hollywood\, performing in small-town lounges\, military bases\, and comedy clubs across the country. His grounded\, down-to-earth humor resonates deeply with audiences\, as he shares stories from his rough childhood\, wild adolescence\, and family life with the skill of a master craftsman. \nHis comedy specials include: \n\n\nBilly Gardell: Halftime (Comedy Central) \n\n\nBilly Gardell Presents Road Dogs (Showtime) \n\n\nA proud Pittsburgh native now living in Los Angeles\, Gardell is a devoted fan of Steelers football\, stand-up comedy\, and his family—his wife Patty and son Will.
URL:https://www.uptowntheatrenapa.com/event/billy-gardell-the-less-is-more-tour/
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://www.uptowntheatrenapa.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Untitled-design-15.png
